##Creating a Gallery

You will have to create a Gallery for both English and French. So these instructions are for English but you would just repeat for french. 

1. Click on the Envira Gallery tab

    ![]({{ images }}Gallery-Menu.png)

2. Click **Add New** at the top

    ![]({{ images }}Gallery-Add-New.png)

3. Enter Title

    ![]({{ images }}Gallery-Title.png)

4. Drop images in the area that says 'Drop Images Here' 

    ![]({{ images }}Gallery-Drop-Images.png)

5. On each image the **'i'** icon can be clicked to edit individual information about the image. EX: Title, Caption.

    ![]({{ images }}Gallery-Update-Info.png)

6. Edit the Title or Caption of the image. Caption will show under the photo in the slideshow. Title is for internal reference.

    ![]({{ images }}Gallery-Update-Caption.png)

7. Update the configuration settings to allows 3 columns of images when displaying the gallery. ( Can have more )

    ![]({{ images }}Gallery-Columns.png)

8. Publish or Save changes.

    ![]({{ images }}Gallery-Publish.png)

9. Get the shortcode. This will be used to put on the Gallery page you create for the website. 

	![]({{ images }}Gallery-Get-Shortcode.png)

10. Copy the code that shows in the highlighted area. 

	![]({{ images }}Gallery-Shortcode.png)

11. Paste this code into the appropriate content section on the gallery page you created. ( See How to Create a Page ). **NOTE:** You need to repeat steps 1 - 10 for French and paste to French code into the french part of the Page. 

	![]({{ images }}Gallery-Add-Shortcode.png)